{{For|the boxing match called Test of Courage|Ray Mercer vs. Tommy Morrison}} {{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Nihongo|'''''Kimodameshi'''''|きもだめし or 肝試し||lit. "test one's liver"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ygzPAAAAMAAJ&q=kimodameshi+liver|title=History of Traditional Medicine: Proceedings of the 1st and 2nd International Symposia on the Comparative History of Medicine--East and West : 1st Symposium: October 22-28, 1976, 2nd Symposium: October 23-29, 1977, Susuno-shi, Shizuoka, Japan|first=Teizō|last=Ogawa|date=April 20, 1986|publisher=Division of Medical History, the Taniguchi Foundation|accessdate=April 20, 2018|via=Google Books}}</ref>}}, or '''test of courage''' is a [[Japan]]ese activity in which people explore scary places to build up [[courage]].<ref>[https://kotobank.jp/word/%E8%82%9D%E8%A9%A6%E3%81%97-475896 肝試し] - コトバンク</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VBHQAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT312&dq=kimodameshi&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjE-5bvmMnaAhVVz2MKHTxmBE4Q6AEINDAC#v=onepage&q=kimodameshi&f=false|title=Tuttle Compact Japanese Dictionary, 2nd Edition: Japanese-English English-Japanese|first=Samuel E.|last=Martin|date=February 12, 2013|publisher=Tuttle Publishing|accessdate=April 20, 2018|via=Google Books}}</ref>
Kimodameshi is usually played in the summer, in group activities such as school club trips or camping. at night, group of people visit scary places such as a [[cemetery]], [[haunted house]], or a forest path to carry out specific missions there.<ref>[https://okinawa.stripes.com/news/kimodameshi-putting-chill-japanese-summer Kimodameshi: Putting a chill in the Japanese summer] - Stripes Okinawa</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JS3rAAAAMAAJ&q=kimodameshi+game&dq=kimodameshi+game&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjA6PfCmMnaAhXHLmMKHfstBn8Q6AEIMjAC|title=Yoshitoshi's Strange Tales|first=John|last=Stevenson|date=April 20, 2018|publisher=Hotei Publishing|accessdate=April 20, 2018|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2016/06/miyamoto_and_the_super_mario_kart_team_on_drifting_battle_mode_and_creating_tension_on_the_track|title=Miyamoto And The Super Mario Kart Team On Drifting, Battle Mode And Creating Tension On The Track|first=Nintendo|last=Life|date=June 29, 2016|website=nintendolife.com|accessdate=April 20, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y9ztAAAAMAAJ&q=kimodameshi+game&dq=kimodameshi+game&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjA6PfCmMnaAhXHLmMKHfstBn8Q6AEIKTAA|title=The Orient strikes back: a global view of cultural display|first=Joy|last=Hendry|date=October 1, 2000|publisher=Berg|accessdate=April 20, 2018|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mHvYAAAAMAAJ&q=kimodameshi+game&dq=kimodameshi+game&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjA6PfCmMnaAhXHLmMKHfstBn8Q6AEILjAB|title=The Children's Folklore Review|author=|date=April 20, 2018|publisher=East Carolina University|accessdate=April 20, 2018|via=Google Books}}</ref>
