26 | Bobby Leach, an American stunt performer, died after a botched amputation of the infected leg which he had broken after slipping on an orange peel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://niagarafallsmuseums.ca/discover-our-history/history-notes/bobbyleach.aspx |title=Bobby Leach|publisher=Niagara Falls Museums|accessdate=18 January 2018|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118064722/https://niagarafallsmuseums.ca/discover-our-history/history-notes/bobbyleach.aspx |archivedate=18 January 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> |- !scope="row" | Phillip McClean | | 1926 | Phillip McClean, aged 16, and his brother were clubbing a [[cassowary]] on the family property in [[Mossman, Queensland]],<ref>{{cite book|last=Christensen|first=Liana |title=Deadly Beautiful: Vanishing Killers of the Animal Kingdom|year=2011|publisher=Exisle Publishing|location=Wollombi, NSW|isbn=978-1-921497-22-3|page=272}}</ref> when the bird knocked him down, kicked him in the neck, and opened a large cut, killing McClean instantly.<ref>Kofron, Christopher P., Chapman, Angela. (2006) "Causes of mortality to the endangered Southern Cassowary Casuarius casuariusjohnsonii in Queensland, Australia." ''Pacific Conservation Biology'' vol. 12: 175–179</ref> |- !scope="row" | [[Isadora Duncan]] | [[File:Isadora Duncan portrait.jpg|100px|center]] | 14 September 1927 | Isadora Duncan, a dancer, broke her neck when her long scarf caught on the wheel of a car in which she was a passenger.<ref>{{cite news|last=Brown|first=Ismene |title=Isadora Duncan, Sublime or Ridiculous?|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/theatre/dance/4949201/Isadora-Duncan-sublime-or-ridiculous.html|work=The Telegraph|date=6 March 2009|accessdate=26 April 2013|location=London|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007094636/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/theatre/dance/4949201/Isadora-Duncan-sublime-or-ridiculous.html |archivedate=7 October 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> |}
=== 1950s === * 1951: '''[[Mary Reeser|Mary Hardy Reeser]]''', 67, was found "virtually [[Cremation|cremated]]" in her otherwise relatively unharmed apartment in [[St. Petersburg, Florida|St. Petersburg]], [[Florida]], leaving a left foot in an undamaged black satin slipper, a shrunken portion of her skull and part of her spine. The [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]] report at the time stated that she had apparently fallen asleep while smoking, setting fire to her [[acetate]] nightgown, housecoat, and chair.<ref>[http://www.tampabay.com/news/humaninterest/fbi-said-1951-death-wasnt-spontaneous-human-combustion-but-mystery-persists/1050679 FBI said 1951 death wasn't 'spontaneous human combustion,' but mystery persists] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140601005035/http://www.tampabay.com/news/humaninterest/fbi-said-1951-death-wasnt-spontaneous-human-combustion-but-mystery-persists/1050679 |date=1 June 2014 }}, ''[[Tampa Bay Times]]''</ref> * 1958: '''[[Gareth Jones (actor)|Gareth Jones]]''', an actor, died of a heart attack between scenes of a live television play, ''[[Underground (1958 TV play)|Underground]]''. Other members of the cast improvised lines, such as "I'm sure if So‑and‑so were here he would say..." to compensate for Jones's absence. Coincidentally, Jones's character was supposed to die of a heart attack in a later scene of the play.<ref>Cited by Gareth Rubin [https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2009/may/31/television-drama-theatre "Live TV drama is resurrected as Sky shrugs off lessons of history",] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170410133156/https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2009/may/31/television-drama-theatre |date=10 April 2017 }} ''The Guardian'', 31 May 2009</ref><ref name="Murray2003">{{cite web|url=http://enjoyment.independent.co.uk/books/reviews/story.jsp?story=426412 |title=''Do Not Adjust Your Set''{{nnbsp}} By Kate Dunn: Live television drama may have gone, but, says Matthew Sweet, this entertaining history ensures it won't be forgotten |website=The Independent |date=20 July 2003 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20030810022829/http://enjoyment.independent.co.uk/books/reviews/story.jsp?story=426412 |archive-date=10 August 2003 |dead-url=yes |first=John |last=Murray |location=London |issn=0951-9467 |quote=An incident on the set of a 1958 edition of Armchair Theatre illustrates the perverse extremes of professionalism that television actors were expected to exhibit. The ... cast included ... a young Welsh actor named Gareth Jones. 'During transmission', recalls {{bracket|Peter}} Bowles, 'a little group of us was talking on camera while awaiting the arrival of Gareth Jones's character [...] We could see him coming up towards us, and he was going to arrive on cue, but we saw him drop, we saw him fall. We had no idea what had happened, but he certainly wasn't coming our way. The actors, including me, started making up lines: "I'm sure if So‑and‑so were here he would say..."' Jones had suffered a fatal heart attack—but rather than informing the actors of their colleague's death and ceasing transmission of the play, the producers decided to let them stumble on to the end. |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
=== 1960s === * 1961: [[United States Army|U.S. Army]] specialists '''John A. Byrnes''' and '''Richard Leroy McKinley''' and [[United States Navy|Navy]] electrician's mate '''Richard C. Legg''' were killed by a [[water hammer]] explosion during maintenance on the [[SL-1]] nuclear reactor in Idaho.<ref>[https://archive.org/details/gov.ntis.A13886VNB1 SL-1 The Accident: Phases I and II] U.S. Atomic Energy Commission Idaho Operations Office video ([https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIBQMkd96CA Youtube 1] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160619011318/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIBQMkd96CA |date=19 June 2016 }}) ([https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BVr6bD-z9hM Youtube 2] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504024316/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BVr6bD-z9hM |date=4 May 2016 }})</ref><ref>[http://www.inl.gov/proving-the-principle/chapter_15.pdf Chapter 15 "The SL-1 Reactor" (page 142)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807212441/http://www.inl.gov/proving-the-principle/chapter_15.pdf |date=7 August 2011 }} 9.5 MB PDF</ref><ref name="Tucker">{{cite book |last=Tucker |first=Todd |title=Atomic America: How a Deadly Explosion and a Feared Admiral Changed the Course of Nuclear History|isbn=978-1-4165-4433-3 |year=2009 |publisher=Free Press |location=New York}} See summary: {{cite web |url=http://catdir.loc.gov/catdir/enhancements/fy0904/2008013842-s.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-20 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721044652/http://catdir.loc.gov/catdir/enhancements/fy0904/2008013842-s.html |archivedate=21 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=McKeown |first=William |title=Idaho Falls: The Untold Story of America's First Nuclear Accident |isbn=978-1-55022-562-4 |year=2003 |publisher=ECW Press |location=Toronto}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/04/business/media/04bingham.html |title=Barry Bingham Jr., Louisville Publisher, Is Dead at 72|work=The New York Times|date=4 April 2006|first=Robert D.|last=McFadden|accessdate=11 May 2010|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130530080731/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/04/04/business/media/04bingham.html |archivedate=30 May 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 1966: '''[[Nick Piantanida]]''', a skydiver, died four months after an attempt to break the record for the highest parachute jump; his suit had depressurized causing brain damage.<ref>{{cite book |title=Magnificent Failure: Free Fall from the Edge of Space |last1=Ryan |first1=Craig |publisher=Smithsonian Air and Space Museum Press |year=2003| isbn=978-1-58834-141-9 |oclc=51059086 }}</ref><ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/article687679.ece Dive Hard] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160820224934/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/article687679.ece |date=20 August 2016 }}, [[The Globe and Mail]], 25 May 2008</ref>
=== 1970s === * 1971: '''[[Georgy Dobrovolsky]]''', '''[[Vladislav Volkov]]''', and '''[[Viktor Patsayev]]''', Soviet cosmonauts, died when their [[Soyuz 11|Soyuz-11]] spacecraft depressurized during preparations for re-entry. These are the only known human deaths outside the Earth's atmosphere.<ref>"[https://web.archive.org/web/20081012062830/http://www.channel4.com/history/microsites/H/history/n-s/space.html%20 Space disasters and near misses]". Channel 4. Archived from [http://www.channel4.com/programmes/categories/history the original] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425182424/http://www.channel4.com/programmes/categories/history |date=25 April 2014 }} on 12 October 2008. Retrieved 29 June 2011.</ref> * 1974: '''Basil Brown''', a 48-year-old health food advocate from [[Croydon]], England, died from liver damage after he consumed 70 million [[International unit|units]] of Vitamin A and around {{convert|10|gal|l|abbr=off}} of [[carrot juice]] over ten days, turning his skin bright yellow.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=yLQsAAAAIBAJ&sjid=jAoEAAAAIBAJ&dq=unusual-death&pg=6515%2C4463628 |work=Star-News |location=Wilmington, North Carolina |title=Unusual death |date=20 February 1974 |accessdate=12 June 2010|page=28}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Staub |first=Jack E. |title=Alluring Lettuces: And Other Seductive Vegetables for Your Garden |year=2005 |publisher=Gibbs Smith|location=Layton, Utah |isbn=978-1-4236-0829-5|oclc=435711200 |page=230 |chapter=74. Yellowstone Carrot: Daucus carota savicus|chapterurl=https://books.google.com/booksid=qbMz7YrTBMEC&lpg=PA230&dq=bl&pg=PA230#v=onepage&q=%22Basil%20Brown%22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1974/02/17/archives/carrotjuice-addiction-cited-in-britons-death.html |title=Carrot-Juice Addiction Cited in Briton's Death|last=|first=|date=February 17, 1974|work=The New York Times|access-date=November 24, 2017|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201055854/http://www.nytimes.com/1974/02/17/archives/carrotjuice-addiction-cited-in-britons-death.html |archivedate=1 December 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 1975: After watching the "[[Kung Fu Kapers]]" episode of ''[[The Goodies (TV series)|The Goodies]]'', a man named '''Alex Mitchell''' laughed continuously for 25 minutes and then fell dead on his sofa from heart failure.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snopes.com/horrors/freakish/laughing.asp |title=Death by Laughing|date=22 June 2012|publisher=}}</ref><ref>''The Complete Goodies'' — Robert Ross, B T Batsford, London, 2000.</ref><ref>''Man Dies Laughing at The Goodies'', "Daily Mail", London (29 March 1975)</ref><ref>''A Goodies Way to Go — Laughing'', "Eastern Daily Press", Norwich (29 March 1975)</ref><ref>''Slapstick! The Illustrated Story of Knockabout Comedy'' — Tony Staveacre, Angus & Robinson 1987</ref> * 1977: '''Tina Christopherson''' died when she fanatically [[water intoxication|drank 4 gallons (15 litres) of water a day]] to combat stomach cancer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/19470900 |title=The Naples Daily News from Naples, Florida · Page 2|website=Newspapers.com|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180624210129/https://www.newspapers.com/newspage/19470900 |archivedate=24 June 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 1977: '''[[Tom Pryce]]''', a driver in the [[1977 South African Grand Prix]], was killed alongside fire marshal '''Frederick Jansen Van Vuuren''' after being struck on the head by a [[fire extinguisher]] when his car, travelling at {{convert|170|mph}}, hit Jansen Van Vuuren as he was running across the [[Kyalami]] race track to extinguish a burning car.<ref>{{citation |title=Thinning the Herd: Tales of the Weirdly Departed |author=Cynthia Ceilán |publisher=Globe Pequot |year=2007 |isbn=978-1-59921-691-1 |page=185}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=The tragedy of Tom Pryce, Wales' Formula One hero |date=4 March 2012 |author=James Roberts |publisher=BBC Wales |quote=one of the most bizarre, tragic accidents in the sport's history}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Strange Deaths |isbn=978-0-09-941660-9 |author=John Dunning |year=1995}}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=Strange Deaths: More Than 375 Freakish Fatalities |isbn=978-0-7607-1947-3 |year=2000|last1=Stevenson |first1=Val }}</ref> * 1978: '''[[Kurt Gödel]]''', the Austrian-American logician and mathematician, died of starvation when his wife was hospitalized. Gödel refused to eat food prepared by anyone else.<ref>Toates, Frederick; Olga Coschug Toates (2002). Obsessive Compulsive Disorder: Practical Tried-and-Tested Strategies to Overcome OCD. Class Publishing, 221. {{ISBN|978-1-85959-069-0}}.</ref> * 1979: '''[[Robert Williams (robot fatality)|Robert Williams]]''', a worker at a Ford Motor Co. plant, became the first person known to be killed by a robot<ref name="rlid">Robot firm liable in death, Tim Kiska, ''The Oregonian'', 11 August 1983.</ref> when the arm of a factory robot struck him in the head.<ref name="a">{{cite news|last=Kiska|first=Tim |title=Death on the job: Jury awards $10 million to heirs of man killed by robot at auto plant |pages=A10|work=[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]] |date=11 August 1983|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/g/GooglePM/PI/lib00187,0EB295F7D995F801.html |accessdate=11 September 2007}}</ref> * 1979: '''John Bowen''', a 20-year-old from [[Nashua, New Hampshire]], was killed at a half-time show at [[Shea Stadium]] when a {{convert|40|lb|adj=on}} model plane shaped like a lawnmower crashed into the stands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snopes.com/horrors/freakish/lawnmower.asp |title=Flying Lawnmower Death – Grim Reaper (contains additional references) |publisher=Snopes.com |date= |accessdate=8 August 2011}}</ref><ref name="Gergen2008">{{cite web|url=http://www.newsday.com/sports/it-was-a-grand-stage-for-excitement-1.885658 |title=It was a grand stage for excitement |first=Joe |last=Gergen |website=Newsday |date=26 September 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160118012323/http://www.newsday.com/sports/it-was-a-grand-stage-for-excitement-1.885658 |archive-date=18 January 2016 |dead-url=no |location=Long Island, New York |issn=0278-5587 |df= }}</ref>
=== 1980s === [[File:Tennessee Williams NYWTS.jpg|thumb|Tennessee Williams]] * 1981: '''[[Boris Sagal]]''', a Ukrainian-American film director, died while shooting the TV miniseries ''[[World War III (miniseries)|World War III]]'' in [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]], Oregon, when he walked into the [[tail rotor]] blade of a helicopter and was partially [[decapitation|decapitated]].<ref>{{cite news| url=https://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F40911FE3E5C0C778EDDAC0894D9484D81 |work=The New York Times |title=Boris Sagal, 58, Movie Director, Dies After A Helicopter Accident|date=24 May 1981|accessdate=11 May 2010|first=Shawn G. |last=Kennedy}}</ref><ref name="salon1">{{cite web|url=http://open.salon.com/blog/jrobertg/2009/07/08/10_strange_celebrity_deaths |title=10 Strange Celebrity Deaths – J. Robert Godbout |publisher=Open Salon |date=8 July 2009 |accessdate=27 September 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130407163600/http://open.salon.com/blog/jrobertg/2009/07/08/10_strange_celebrity_deaths |archivedate=7 April 2013 |df= }}</ref> * 1982: '''David Grundman''', [[Cactus plugging|shooting at cacti]] with his shotgun near [[Lake Pleasant Regional Park|Lake Pleasant]], Arizona, was crushed when a {{convert|4|ft|adj=on}} limb of the cactus detached and fell on him.<ref name="salon1" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snopes.com/horrors/freakish/saguaro.asp |title=Cactus Courageous – Death by Saguaro |publisher=Snopes.com |date= |accessdate=8 August 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/content/printVersion/160293 |title=When Cactus and Civilization collide – Trifling with Saguaros can be Hazardous to one's Health |publisher=Phoenixnewtimes.com |date=3 March 1993 |accessdate=8 August 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810041817/http://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/content/printVersion/160293/ |archivedate=10 August 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> * 1983: '''[[Tennessee Williams]]''', an American playwright, died after accidentally choking on a plastic bottle cap which he was using to ingest barbiturates.<ref>{{cite news |title=Drugs Linked to Death of Tennessee Williams |url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/00/12/31/specials/williams-drugs.html |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=14 August 1983 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170226223629/http://www.nytimes.com/books/00/12/31/specials/williams-drugs.html |archivedate=26 February 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Reports at the time of his death indicated he had died applying eyedrops while holding the cap between his teeth, but this was corrected in the official medical examiner's report six months later.<ref>{{cite news |author=Suzanne Daley |title=Williams Choked on a Bottle Cap |url=https://www.nytimes.com/books/00/12/31/specials/williams-choked.html |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=27 February 1983 |accessdate=18 February 2018 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117180500/http://www.nytimes.com/books/00/12/31/specials/williams-choked.html |archivedate=17 November 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> * 1983: '''Truls Hellevik''', a diver, [[Byford Dolphin#Diving bell accident|exploded into many small parts]] when accidentally exposed to an eight-[[atmosphere (unit)|atmosphere]] change in [[air pressure]], which forced his body through a {{convert|60|cm|in|adj=mid|-diameter}} opening instantaneously.<ref name="pmid3381801">{{cite journal |vauthors=Giertsen JC, Sandstad E, Morild I, Bang G, Bjersand AJ, Eidsvik S |title=An explosive decompression accident |journal=American Journal of Forensic Medicine and Pathology |volume=9 |issue=2 |pages=94–101 |date=June 1988 |pmid=3381801 |doi=10.1097/00000433-198806000-00002}}</ref><ref name=AADreport>{{cite web|publisher=Norwegian Petroleum Directorate |date=27 August 2002 |title=Report to AAD regarding the Byford Dolphin accident |url=http://www.npd.no/English/Aktuelt/Nyheter/aad_redegjorelse.htm |accessdate=24 March 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070212210351/http://www.npd.no/English/Aktuelt/Nyheter/aad_redegjorelse.htm |archivedate=12 February 2007 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> * 1983: '''[[Dick Wertheim]]''', a tennis linesman, died after a ball struck him in the groin and he fell out of his chair.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2005/writers/jon_wertheim/10/19/mailbag/2.html |title=Czech yourself (pt. 3) |accessdate= 17 January 2018 |last=Wertheim |first=Jon |date=2005-10-19 |work=SI.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080130173951/http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2005/writers/jon_wertheim/10/19/mailbag/2.html |archive-date=2008-01-30|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Odd mishap fells tennis official |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=fwIMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=jFkDAAAAIBAJ&pg=7153,2693520 |work=Evening Independent |location=St. Petersburg, Fla. |page=3-C |date=12 September 1983 |accessdate=17 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tennis serve kills official|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=kXImAAAAIBAJ&sjid=gv4FAAAAIBAJ&pg=4816,1253853&dq=dick+wertheim+tennis|accessdate=17 January 2018|newspaper=The Afro American|date=24 September 1983}}</ref> * 1983: '''Jimmy Ferrozzo''', a bouncer, died in [[Condor Club]], San Francisco while engaging in sexual intercourse with his girlfriend Theresa Hill on a [[grand piano]] that was lowered from the ceiling by a hydraulic motor. Ferrozzo accidentally activated the lifting mechanism which pinned him against the ceiling leading to his suffocation.<ref name="nyt">{{cite web |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/15/us/15bcintel.html |title= Condor Club {{!}} North Beach, San Francisco |website= [[The New York Times]] |accessdate= 18 January 2018 |deadurl= no |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20180118064649/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/15/us/15bcintel.html |archivedate= 18 January 2018 |df= dmy-all }}</ref> Hill survived the accident.<ref name="nyt"/> * 1987: '''Paul G. Thomas''', owner of a wool mill in [[Thompson, Connecticut]], died of suffocation after falling into a machine in the wool mill and becoming wrapped in {{convert|800|yd}} of wool.<ref>{{cite news |title=Man Falls Into Wool Machine, Is Covered in Yarn, Suffocates |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1987-08-13/news/mn-1409_1_yarn |accessdate=30 June 2018 |work=Los Angeles Times |date=13 August 1987 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171130032627/http://articles.latimes.com/1987-08-13/news/mn-1409_1_yarn |archivedate=30 November 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
=== 1990s === * 1991: A male flight instructor and a female student, '''Carl Beauford Terry''' and '''Linda Varnar Keath''',<ref>{{cite web |title=A "Mile High" Fatality... |url=http://www.check-six.com/Crash_Sites/N47506-MileHigh.htm |website=Check-Six.com}}</ref> were killed when the [[Piper PA-34 Seneca]] airplane they were flying crashed, believed to have been caused by the two people having sex in the cockpit of the plane.<ref>{{cite web |title=NTSB Identification: MIA92FA051|url=https://www.ntsb.gov/_layouts/ntsb.aviation/brief.aspx?ev_id=20001212X18632|website=www.NTSB.gov|publisher=National Transit Safety Board|accessdate=15 May 2018|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180516103623/https://www.ntsb.gov/_layouts/ntsb.aviation/brief.aspx?ev_id=20001212X18632 |archivedate=16 May 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Movements in the cockpit led to the [[Yoke (aeronautics)|stick]] being pushed down and the airplane exceeding its speed limitations and breaking off the right wing. * 1993: '''[[Brandon Lee]]''', 28-year-old film actor, martial artist, and son of [[Bruce Lee]], was accidentally shot to death by co-star [[Michael Massee]] while filming a scene for ''[[The Crow (1994 film)|The Crow]]'', as the result of an [[squib load|improperly-loaded]] prop gun.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/04/15/movies/bruce-lee-s-brief-life-being-brought-to-screen.html |title=Bruce Lee's Brief Life Being Brought to Screen |first=Bernard |last=Weinraub |publisher=''The New York Times'' |date=15 April 1993 |accessdate=19 August 2016 |quote="Referring to the bizarre death of Brandon Lee, he said: 'This latest tragedy is almost too much. I don't know what to make of it. It's almost like something unseen is taking place that's more than a coincidence.'" |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827060836/http://www.nytimes.com/1993/04/15/movies/bruce-lee-s-brief-life-being-brought-to-screen.html |archivedate=27 August 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1993/04/01/the-reliable-source/8493d280-e88c-427a-aa9b-634b170fe626/ |title=The Reliable Source |publisher=''The Washington Post'' |date=1 April 1993 |accessdate=19 August 2016 |quote="Hollywood was aghast yesterday over the sudden and bizarre death of 27-year-old actor Brandon Lee, who was filming in Wilmington, N.C." |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160914202229/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1993/04/01/the-reliable-source/8493d280-e88c-427a-aa9b-634b170fe626/ |archivedate=14 September 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/film/the-crow/brandon-lee-death-shooting-truth |title=Brandon Lee and the 'curse' of The Crow|first=Tim|last=Robey|publisher=''The Telegraph''|date=30 October 2015|accessdate=19 August 2016|quote="The accident that had just occurred may be the unluckiest in the history of Hollywood production, for a bleak variety of logistical reasons that only came to light afterwards. It was also among the eeriest and most tragic in a whole set of other ways."|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808100440/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/film/the-crow/brandon-lee-death-shooting-truth |archivedate=8 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 1993: '''[[Garry Hoy]]''', a lawyer in [[Toronto]], Ontario, fell to his death from the 24th floor of the [[Toronto-Dominion Centre]] while demonstrating to a group of visitors that the building's windows were "unbreakable". Hoy threw himself against the window, which indeed did not break—but it popped out of its frame.<ref>[http://www.snopes.com/horrors/freakish/window.asp Window Test Death – Through a Glass, Quickly] at Snopes.com</ref><ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/goodman-and-carr-falls-prey-to-rivals/article17993183/ Goodman and Carr falls prey to rivals] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161211122916/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/report-on-business/goodman-and-carr-falls-prey-to-rivals/article17993183/ |date=11 December 2016 }} by Jacquie McNish, The Globe and Mail, 15 March 2007.</ref> * 1994: '''[[Death of Gloria Ramirez|Gloria Ramirez]]''', 31, died from [[kidney failure]] related to her [[cervical cancer]]. While treating her, several of the hospital staff became ill, suffering from loss of consciousness, shortness of breath and muscle spasms. Shortly before dying, Ramirez was allegedly covered with an oily sheen, which smelled of fruit and garlic. When drawing her blood with a syringe, nurses noticed it had a smell similar to [[ammonia]] and there were unusual particles floating in it.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Stone|first1=Richard |title=Analysis of a Toxic Death|url=http://discovermagazine.com/1995/apr/analysisofatoxic493|accessdate=7 April 2018|work=Discover Magazine|date=April 1995|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429152718/http://discovermagazine.com/1995/apr/analysisofatoxic493 |archivedate=29 April 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 1994: '''Jeremy Brenno''', 16, was killed on a golf course when, frustrated, he struck a bench with a 3-wood golf club. The shaft broke, bounced back at him, and pierced his heart.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.snopes.com/sports/golf/shafted.asp | title=Shafted | publisher=[[Snopes]] | accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref> * 1997: '''[[Karen Wetterhahn]]''', a professor of chemistry at [[Dartmouth College]], died ten months after a few drops of [[dimethylmercury]] landed on her protective gloves. Although Wetterhahn had been following the required procedures, the material permeated the gloves and her skin within seconds.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chm.bris.ac.uk/motm/dimethylmercury/dmmh.htm |title=Dimethylmercury and Mercury Poisoning |publisher=Chm.bris.ac.uk |date= |accessdate=16 November 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/66yo4jiX6?url=http://www.chm.bris.ac.uk/motm/dimethylmercury/dmmh.htm |archivedate=17 April 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iaomt.org/testfoundation/dimethylmercury.htm |title=The Trembling Edge of Science |publisher=Iaomt.org |date= |accessdate=16 November 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111114004559/http://www.iaomt.org/testfoundation/dimethylmercury.htm |archivedate=14 November 2011 |df= }}</ref><ref name="Loback1997">{{cite web|url=http://thedartmouth.com/1997/02/24/accident-hospitalizes-wetterhahn/ |title=Accident hospitalizes Wetterhahn |website=The Dartmouth |date=24 February 1997 |archive-date=7 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107144442/http://thedartmouth.com/1997/02/24/accident-hospitalizes-wetterhahn/ |dead-url=no |first=Erin |last=Loback |location=Hanover, New Hampshire |issn=0199-9931 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> * 1998: '''Jonathan Capewell''', 16, died from a heart attack brought on by the buildup of [[butane]] and [[propane]] in the blood after excessive use of [[deodorant]] sprays.<ref name="capewell">{{cite web| url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/health/203730.stm| title =Health Deodorant obsession killed boy| publisher =BBC| date =October 29, 1998| accessdate =18 January 2018| deadurl =no| archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20180118070357/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/health/203730.stm| archivedate =18 January 2018| df =dmy-all}}</ref> Capewell was reported to have an obsession with personal hygiene.<ref name="capewell"/> An autopsy showed that Capewell had 0.37 mg of butane per litre in his blood, and the same amount of propane, whereas 0.1 mg per litre can be fatal.<ref name="capewell"/> * 1999: '''Betty Stobbs''', 67, died after delivering a bale of hay to her [[sheep]]. The starving sheep rushed Stobbs, who was on her [[motorcycle]]. In the ensuing scuffle, Stobbs was knocked down into a deep [[ravine]] near [[Durham, England]]. While she survived the fall, her motorcycle landed on her, killing her instantly.<ref name="news99">{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1999/jan/29/news/mn-2886 |title=Death by Sheep|website=Sheep Push Woman Over Edge of Cliff|accessdate=23 June 2018|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619132205/http://articles.latimes.com/1999/jan/29/news/mn-2886 |archivedate=19 June 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
== 21st century == === 2000s === * 2001: '''[[Bernd Brandes]]''', a German [[engineer]] from Berlin, was willingly slaughtered so that he could be butchered and eaten by aspiring [[Cannibalism|cannibal]] [[Armin Meiwes]]. Brandes had responded to an internet advertisement which Meiwes had placed for this purpose. In prison, Meiwes became a vegetarian.<ref name="news0">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/3286721.stm|work=[[BBC News]] |title=German cannibal tells of fantasy|accessdate=9 July 2007|date=3 December 2003|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070826063317/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/3286721.stm |archivedate=26 August 2007|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/4039034 |title=NBC: Cannibal trial shocks Germany – World news – NBC News|website=msnbc.com|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025204955/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/4039034 |archivedate=25 October 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2004/01/19/1074360665924.html |title=Cannibal trial reveals perverse intimacy|website=theage.com.au|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171206011900/http://www.theage.com.au/articles/2004/01/19/1074360665924.html |archivedate=6 December 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> *2003: '''[[Brian Douglas Wells]]''', a pizza delivery man from [[Erie, Pennsylvania]], was killed by an explosive collar around his neck, as part of a bank-robbery scheme.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/pizza-bomb-update-marjorie-diehl-armstrong-sentenced-to-life-for-bizarre-pa-collar-bomb-killing| title="Pizza Bomb" Update: Marjorie Diehl-Armstrong sentenced to life for bizarre Pa. collar-bomb killing| date=March 2, 2011| work=CBS News| deadurl=no| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823204124/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/pizza-bomb-update-marjorie-diehl-armstrong-sentenced-to-life-for-bizarre-pa-collar-bomb-killing| archivedate=23 August 2017| df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 2004: '''Phillip Quinn''', 24, from [[Kent, Washington|Kent]], Washington, was killed when a [[lava lamp]] he was heating on a stove exploded, with a shard piercing his heart.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.snopes.com/horrors/freakish/lavalamp.asp | title=Lava Lamp Death | publisher=[[Snopes]] | accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref> * 2005: '''[[Kenneth Pinyan]]''' died from injuries caused by [[anal sex]] with a [[stallion]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sokol |first1=Zach |title=The Strange, Sad Story of the Man Named Mr. Hands Who Died from Having Sex with a Horse |url=https://www.vice.com/read/ten-years-ago-mr-hands-got-fucked-to-death-by-a-horse-716 |website=Vice |publisher=Vice.com |accessdate=25 March 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6f7zktS4B?url=http://www.vice.com/read/ten-years-ago-mr-hands-got-fucked-to-death-by-a-horse-716 |archivedate=7 February 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> * 2007: '''Humberto Hernandez''', a 24-year-old [[Oakland, California|Oakland]], California resident, was killed after being struck in the face by an airborne [[fire hydrant]] while walking. A passing car had struck the fire hydrant and the water pressure shot the hydrant at Hernandez with enough force to kill him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snopes.com/horrors/freakish/hydrant.asp |title=Fire Hydrant Death – Fire Plugged |publisher=Snopes.com |date= |accessdate=8 August 2011}}</ref><ref name="Harris2007">{{cite web|url=http://www.insidebayarea.com/oaklandtribune/localnews/ci_6212632 |title=Flying fire hydrant kills man |website=Oakland Tribune |date=23 June 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709193834/http://www.insidebayarea.com/oaklandtribune/localnews/ci_6212632 |archive-date=9 July 2015 |dead-url=no |first=Harry |last=Harris |issn=1068-5936 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/offbeat/2007-06-23-fire-hydrant_N.htm |title=Flying fire hydrant kills Calif. man |work=USA Today |date=23 June 2007 |accessdate=8 August 2011 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819081915/http://www.usatoday.com/news/offbeat/2007-06-23-fire-hydrant_N.htm |archivedate=19 August 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> * 2008: '''Judy Kay Zagorski''' was killed when a {{convert|75|lb|adj=on}} [[spotted eagle ray]] leapt out of the water and knocked her over. The ray also died.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/7308839.stm |title=Leaping ray kills Florida boater|publisher=BBC News|date=21 March 2008|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080325073745/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/7308839.stm |archivedate=25 March 2008|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2008/US/03/21/eagleray/index.html |title=Blunt force trauma killed woman struck by ray|publisher=CNN|date=21 March 2008|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107144442/http://edition.cnn.com/2008/US/03/21/eagleray/index.html |archivedate=7 January 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/23727914/ns/us_news-life/t/stingray-kills-woman-boat-florida-keys |title=Stingray kills woman on boat|publisher=NBC News|date=20 March 2008|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202015025/http://www.nbcnews.com/id/23727914/ns/us_news-life/t/stingray-kills-woman-boat-florida-keys |archivedate=2 February 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 2008: '''David Phyall''', 50, the last resident in a block of flats due to be demolished in [[Bishopstoke]], near [[Southampton]], [[Hampshire]], England, decapitated himself with a [[chainsaw]] to highlight the injustice of being forced to move out.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/death-was-carefully-thought-through-suicide-1025503.html |title=Chainsaw death was 'carefully thought through suicide'|last=Halfpenny|first=Martin|date=19 November 2008|work=The Independent|accessdate=22 November 2008|location=London|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081230040547/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/death-was-carefully-thought-through-suicide-1025503.html |archivedate=30 December 2008|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/hampshire/7737721.stm |publisher=BBC News | title=Man cut off head in flat protest | date=19 November 2008}}</ref> *2008: A 43-year-old Irish mother of four died of an allergic reaction after having sex with a [[German Shepherd]] dog.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/08/woman-dies-allergic-sex-with-dog_n_893509.html |title=Woman Died From Sex With Dog, Sean McDonnell Arrested In Limerick, Ireland|work=The Huffington Post|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721052858/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/08/woman-dies-allergic-sex-with-dog_n_893509.html |archivedate=21 July 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> *2009: '''[[Taylor Mitchell]]''', a 19-year-old [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[folk music|folk singer]], was killed by a pair of coyotes while hiking in [[Cape Breton Highlands National Park]], in the only known fatal coyote attack on an adult.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/coyotes-kill-toronto-singer-in-cape-breton-1.779304 |title=Coyotes kill Toronto singer in Cape Breton|publisher=''CBC News''|date=29 October 2009|accessdate=22 August 2016|quote="Bob Bancroft, a retired biologist with the Department of Natural Resources, said this kind of attack is extremely rare..."|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818213000/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/nova-scotia/coyotes-kill-toronto-singer-in-cape-breton-1.779304 |archivedate=18 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.explore-mag.com/when-coyotes-attack |title=When coyotes attack |publisher=''Explore'' |date=22 February 2010 |accessdate=22 August 2016 |quote="As headline writers across the continent tried to marry some unfamiliar words—fatal, coyote, mauling—most people who spend time outdoors found it hard to believe that coyotes had actually killed a human." |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160811062752/http://www.explore-mag.com/when-coyotes-attack |archivedate=11 August 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2009/oct/30/taylor-mitchell-coyote-death-rare |title=Coyote killings are rare and shocking|first=Colin|last=Horgan|publisher=''The Guardian''|date=30 October 2009|accessdate=22 August 2016|quote="Singer Taylor Mitchell's death was highly unusual ... [D]espite the frequency of coyote encounters, attacks are rarely very serious, and deaths as a result are virtually unheard of."|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130908034410/http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2009/oct/30/taylor-mitchell-coyote-death-rare |archivedate=8 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
