antly from [[pneumothorax]] brought on by exposure to very high levels of leaked oxygen.<ref name="week"/> Conflicting reports state two or three hospital employees were arrested for [[negligence]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/indian-man-killed-being-sucked-mri-machine-075255842.html |title=Indian man killed after being sucked into MRI machine|access-date=2018-01-30|language=en-US|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180130002218/https://www.yahoo.com/news/indian-man-killed-being-sucked-mri-machine-075255842.html |archivedate=30 January 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name="week" /> The [[Maharashtra]] state government compensated Maru's family 500,000 [[Indian rupee|rupees]].<ref name=":1" /> * 2018: '''[[Death of Elaine Herzberg|Elaine Herzberg]]''', a 49-year-old woman in [[Tempe, Arizona]], died after being hit by a [[Autonomous car|self-driving car]] operated by [[Uber]], as she crossed the road, in what was reported to be the first death of a pedestrian struck by a self-driving car on public roads. In response to the fatal accident, Uber suspended self-driving car tests in all U.S. cities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2018/mar/19/uber-self-driving-car-kills-woman-arizona-tempe |title=Self-driving Uber kills Arizona woman in first fatal crash involving pedestrian|publisher=The Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-43459156 |title=Uber halts self-driving car tests after death|publisher=BBC|deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328013839/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-43459156 |archivedate=28 March 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> * 2018: '''Ateef Rafiq''', 24, died from [[cardiac arrest]] in [[Birmingham]], [[England]] whilst looking for his dropped [[mobile phone]]. His head became wedged under the electronic footrest of a [[Movie theater|cinema]] seat.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/mar/20/man-dies-after-getting-trap